146 const char*
147 IoCtlString(
148  ULONG IoControlCode
149 )
150 {
151  ULONG FuncCode = ((IoControlCode >> 2) & 0xFFF) - 100;
152  return FuncCode < ARRAYSIZE(IoCtls) ? IoCtls[FuncCode].Name : "UNKNOWN IOCTL";
153 }

155 // Handles queries for the current list of Thread interfaces
156 _IRQL_requires_max_(PASSIVE_LEVEL)
157 NTSTATUS
158 otLwfIoCtlEnumerateInterfaces(
159  _In_reads_bytes_(InBufferLength)
160  PVOID InBuffer,
161  _In_ ULONG InBufferLength,
162  _Out_writes_bytes_(*OutBufferLength)
163  PVOID OutBuffer,
164  _Inout_ PULONG OutBufferLength
165  )
166 {
167  NTSTATUS status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
168  ULONG NewOutBufferLength = 0;
169  POTLWF_INTERFACE_LIST pInterfaceList = (POTLWF_INTERFACE_LIST)OutBuffer;
170 
171  UNREFERENCED_PARAMETER(InBuffer);
172  UNREFERENCED_PARAMETER(InBufferLength);
173 
174  LogFuncEntry(DRIVER_IOCTL);
175 
176  // Make sure to zero out the output first
177  RtlZeroMemory(OutBuffer, *OutBufferLength);
178 
179  NdisAcquireSpinLock(&FilterListLock);
180 
181  // Make sure there is enough space for the first uint16_t
182  if (*OutBufferLength < sizeof(uint16_t))
183  {
184  status = STATUS_BUFFER_TOO_SMALL;
185  goto error;
186  }
187 
188  // Iterate through each interface and build up the list of running interfaces
189  for (PLIST_ENTRY Link = FilterModuleList.Flink; Link != &FilterModuleList; Link = Link->Flink)
190  {
191  PMS_FILTER pFilter = CONTAINING_RECORD(Link, MS_FILTER, FilterModuleLink);
192  if (pFilter->State != FilterRunning) continue;
193 
194  PGUID pInterfaceGuid = &pInterfaceList->InterfaceGuids[pInterfaceList->cInterfaceGuids];
195  pInterfaceList->cInterfaceGuids++;
196 
197  NewOutBufferLength =
198  FIELD_OFFSET(OTLWF_INTERFACE_LIST, InterfaceGuids) +
199  pInterfaceList->cInterfaceGuids * sizeof(GUID);
200 
201  if (NewOutBufferLength <= *OutBufferLength)
202  {
203  *pInterfaceGuid = pFilter->InterfaceGuid;
204  }
205  }
206 
207  if (NewOutBufferLength > *OutBufferLength)
208  {
209  NewOutBufferLength = sizeof(USHORT);
210  }
211 
212 error:
213 
214  NdisReleaseSpinLock(&FilterListLock);
215 
216  *OutBufferLength = NewOutBufferLength;
217 
218  LogFuncExitNT(DRIVER_IOCTL, status);
219 
220  return status;
221 }

223 // Handles queries for the details of a specific Thread interface
224 _IRQL_requires_max_(PASSIVE_LEVEL)
225 NTSTATUS
226 otLwfIoCtlQueryInterface(
227  _In_reads_bytes_(InBufferLength)
228  PVOID InBuffer,
229  _In_ ULONG InBufferLength,
230  _Out_writes_bytes_(*OutBufferLength)
231  PVOID OutBuffer,
232  _Inout_ PULONG OutBufferLength
233  )
234 {
235  NTSTATUS status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
236  ULONG NewOutBufferLength = 0;
237 
238  LogFuncEntry(DRIVER_IOCTL);
239 
240  // Make sure there is enough space for the first USHORT
241  if (InBufferLength < sizeof(GUID) || *OutBufferLength < sizeof(OTLWF_DEVICE))
242  {
243  status = STATUS_BUFFER_TOO_SMALL;
244  goto error;
245  }
246 
247  PGUID pInterfaceGuid = (PGUID)InBuffer;
248  POTLWF_DEVICE pDevice = (POTLWF_DEVICE)OutBuffer;
249 
250  // Look up the interface
251  PMS_FILTER pFilter = otLwfFindAndRefInterface(pInterfaceGuid);
252  if (pFilter == NULL)
253  {
254  status = STATUS_DEVICE_DOES_NOT_EXIST;
255  goto error;
256  }
257 
258  NewOutBufferLength = sizeof(OTLWF_DEVICE);
259  pDevice->CompartmentID = pFilter->InterfaceCompartmentID;
260 
261  // Release the ref on the interface
262  ExReleaseRundownProtection(&pFilter->ExternalRefs);
263 
264 error:
265 
266  if (NewOutBufferLength < *OutBufferLength)
267  {
268  RtlZeroMemory((PUCHAR)OutBuffer + NewOutBufferLength, *OutBufferLength - NewOutBufferLength);
269  }
270 
271  *OutBufferLength = NewOutBufferLength;
272 
273  LogFuncExitNT(DRIVER_IOCTL, status);
274 
275  return status;
276 }

278 // Handles IOTCLs for OpenThread control
279 _IRQL_requires_max_(PASSIVE_LEVEL)
280 NTSTATUS
281 otLwfIoCtlOpenThreadControl(
282  _In_ PIRP Irp
283  )
284 {
285  NTSTATUS status = STATUS_PENDING;
286  PMS_FILTER pFilter = NULL;
287 
288  PIO_STACK_LOCATION IrpSp = IoGetCurrentIrpStackLocation(Irp);
289 
290  LogFuncEntry(DRIVER_IOCTL);
291 
292  if (IrpSp->Parameters.DeviceIoControl.InputBufferLength < sizeof(GUID))
293  {
294  status = STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER;
295  goto error;
296  }
297 
298  pFilter = otLwfFindAndRefInterface((PGUID)Irp->AssociatedIrp.SystemBuffer);
299  if (pFilter == NULL)
300  {
301  status = STATUS_DEVICE_DOES_NOT_EXIST;
302  goto error;
303  }
304 
305  if (pFilter->DeviceStatus == OTLWF_DEVICE_STATUS_RADIO_MODE)
306  {
307  // Pend the Irp for processing on the OpenThread event processing thread
308  otLwfEventProcessingIndicateIrp(pFilter, Irp);
309  }
310  else
311  {
312  status = otLwfTunIoCtl(pFilter, Irp);
313  }
314 
315  // Release our ref on the filter
316  ExReleaseRundownProtection(&pFilter->ExternalRefs);
317 
318 error:
319 
320  // Complete the IRP if we aren't pending (indicates we failed)
321  if (status != STATUS_PENDING)
322  {
323  NT_ASSERT(status != STATUS_SUCCESS);
324  RtlZeroMemory(Irp->AssociatedIrp.SystemBuffer, IrpSp->Parameters.DeviceIoControl.OutputBufferLength);
325  Irp->IoStatus.Status = status;
326  IoCompleteRequest(Irp, IO_NO_INCREMENT);
327  }
328 
329  LogFuncExitNT(DRIVER_IOCTL, status);
330 
331  return status;
332 }

334 // Handles Irp for IOTCLs for OpenThread control on the OpenThread thread
335 _IRQL_requires_max_(PASSIVE_LEVEL)
336 VOID
337 otLwfCompleteOpenThreadIrp(
338  _In_ PMS_FILTER pFilter,
339  _In_ PIRP Irp
340  )
341 {
342  PIO_STACK_LOCATION IrpSp = IoGetCurrentIrpStackLocation(Irp);
343 
344  PUCHAR InBuffer = (PUCHAR)Irp->AssociatedIrp.SystemBuffer + sizeof(GUID);
345  PVOID OutBuffer = Irp->AssociatedIrp.SystemBuffer;
346 
347  ULONG InBufferLength = IrpSp->Parameters.DeviceIoControl.InputBufferLength - sizeof(GUID);
348  ULONG OutBufferLength = IrpSp->Parameters.DeviceIoControl.OutputBufferLength;
349  ULONG IoControlCode = IrpSp->Parameters.DeviceIoControl.IoControlCode;
350 
351  ULONG OrigOutBufferLength = OutBufferLength;
352 
353  NTSTATUS status = STATUS_NOT_IMPLEMENTED;
354 
355  ULONG FuncCode = ((IoControlCode >> 2) & 0xFFF) - 100;
356  if (FuncCode < ARRAYSIZE(IoCtls))
357  {
358  LogVerbose(DRIVER_IOCTL, "Processing Irp=%p, for %s (In:%u,Out:%u)",
359  Irp, IoCtls[FuncCode].Name, InBufferLength, OutBufferLength);
360 
361  if (IoCtls[FuncCode].otFunc)
362  {
363  status = IoCtls[FuncCode].otFunc(pFilter, InBuffer, InBufferLength, OutBuffer, &OutBufferLength);
364  }
365  else
366  {
367  OutBufferLength = 0;
368  }
369 
370  LogVerbose(DRIVER_IOCTL, "Completing Irp=%p, with %!STATUS! for %s (Out:%u)",
371  Irp, status, IoCtls[FuncCode].Name, OutBufferLength);
372  }
373  else
374  {
375  OutBufferLength = 0;
376  }
377 
378  // Clear any leftover output buffer
379  if (OutBufferLength < OrigOutBufferLength)
380  {
381  RtlZeroMemory((PUCHAR)OutBuffer + OutBufferLength, OrigOutBufferLength - OutBufferLength);
382  }
383 
384  // Complete the IRP
385  Irp->IoStatus.Information = OutBufferLength;
386  Irp->IoStatus.Status = status;
387  IoCompleteRequest(Irp, IO_NO_INCREMENT);
388 }

390 // Handles Irp for IOTCLs for OpenThread control on the OpenThread thread
391 _IRQL_requires_max_(PASSIVE_LEVEL)
392 NTSTATUS
393 otLwfTunIoCtl(
394  _In_ PMS_FILTER pFilter,
395  _In_ PIRP Irp
396  )
397 {
398  PIO_STACK_LOCATION IrpSp = IoGetCurrentIrpStackLocation(Irp);
399 
400  PUCHAR InBuffer = (PUCHAR)Irp->AssociatedIrp.SystemBuffer + sizeof(GUID);
401  ULONG InBufferLength = IrpSp->Parameters.DeviceIoControl.InputBufferLength - sizeof(GUID);
402  ULONG OutBufferLength = IrpSp->Parameters.DeviceIoControl.OutputBufferLength;
403  ULONG IoControlCode = IrpSp->Parameters.DeviceIoControl.IoControlCode;
404 
405  NTSTATUS status = STATUS_NOT_IMPLEMENTED;
406 
407  ULONG FuncCode = ((IoControlCode >> 2) & 0xFFF) - 100;
408  if (FuncCode < ARRAYSIZE(IoCtls))
409  {
410  LogVerbose(DRIVER_IOCTL, "Processing Irp=%p, for %s (In:%u,Out:%u)",
411  Irp, IoCtls[FuncCode].Name, InBufferLength, OutBufferLength);
412 
413  if (IoCtls[FuncCode].tunFunc)
414  {
415  status = IoCtls[FuncCode].tunFunc(pFilter, Irp, InBuffer, InBufferLength, OutBufferLength);
416  }
417 
418  if (!NT_SUCCESS(status))
419  {
420  LogVerbose(DRIVER_IOCTL, "Completing Irp=%p, with %!STATUS! for %s",
421  Irp, status, IoCtls[FuncCode].Name);
422  }
423  }
424 
425  if (NT_SUCCESS(status))
426  {
427  status = STATUS_PENDING;
428 
429  // Mark the Irp as pending
430  IoMarkIrpPending(Irp);
431  }
432 
433  return status;
434 }

436 _IRQL_requires_max_(PASSIVE_LEVEL)
437 NTSTATUS
438 otLwfIoCtl_otInterface(
439  _In_ PMS_FILTER pFilter,
440  _In_reads_bytes_(InBufferLength)
441  PUCHAR InBuffer,
442  _In_ ULONG InBufferLength,
443  _Out_writes_bytes_(*OutBufferLength)
444  PVOID OutBuffer,
445  _Inout_ PULONG OutBufferLength
446  )
447 {
448  NTSTATUS status = STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER;
449 
450  if (InBufferLength >= sizeof(BOOLEAN))
451  {
452  BOOLEAN IsEnabled = *(BOOLEAN*)InBuffer;
453  if (IsEnabled)
454  {
455  // Make sure our addresses are in sync
456  (void)otLwfInitializeAddresses(pFilter);
457  otLwfRadioAddressesUpdated(pFilter);
458 
459  status = ThreadErrorToNtstatus(otInterfaceUp(pFilter->otCtx));
460  }
461  else
462  {
463  status = ThreadErrorToNtstatus(otInterfaceDown(pFilter->otCtx));
464  }
465 
466  *OutBufferLength = 0;
467  }
468  else if (*OutBufferLength >= sizeof(BOOLEAN))
469  {
470  *(BOOLEAN*)OutBuffer = otIsInterfaceUp(pFilter->otCtx) ? TRUE : FALSE;

1569  if (aLinkMode->mDeviceType) numeric_mode |= kThreadMode_FullFunctionDevice;
